main event: Two cast iron objects weighing 13 3/4 pounds crashed through the roof of the American Oil Company in Baltimore, Maryland on May 7, 1955.
interesting points: The objects were reported to have made a distinctly audible sound upon impact,Investigations suggested the objects possibly came from nearby scrap yard operations,Initial evaluations indicated the pieces were likely of metallic composition but no definitive identification could be determined,The objects were described as being about 2 feet long and not immediately identified as aircraft,There were multiple witnesses including employees of the American Oil Company.
witness description: employees of the American Oil Company
